Hi Allie,
​
Long story short, how things were configured were causing legitimate emails from being identified as spam because they were originating from a mail server that's not listed as one that vsos.com.au would typically send from.

So, for example, imagine if you received a letter from Bob who you know lives in Sydney, yet the return address on the letter is in Perth, you'd chuck it out because you know that Bob wouldn't be sending you letters from Perth. Our email server was doing the same thing.
​
Hope that makes sense?
